markets.title: Will New York City suspend **indoor dining** by January 14?
markets.subtitle: By Jan 14, 2021
markets.rules_primary: If the Office of the Mayor of New York City or the New York State Governor's Office issue a press release announcing the suspension of indoor dining by January 14, 2022 that is implemented prior to Expiration, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
The Contract will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM following the occurrence of an event that is encompassed in the Payout Criterion, or January 15, 2022 at 10:00 AM.

Please see NYCDN in the Rulebook for the complete legally binding terms and conditions.
